The Galco BATTL™ Sling - Bilateral Ambidextrous Tactical Transition for Longarms - was designed for use with long guns in combat and tactical environments. It possesses several key advantages over more conventional three-point and single-point slings.

The primary tactical advantage of the BATTL Sling lies in its ability to quickly and easily transition between strong-side and weak-side firing positions. The speed and ease of this transition is particularly useful in the tactical environment when approaching a corner or obstacle that is most safely negotiated by transitioning from one shoulder to the other, maximizing available cover.

The BATTL Sling’s 2” wide Main Strap helps distribute weight and allows comfortable all-day carry of even a heavy shotgun while still maintaining a posture of complete readiness. The length of the Main Strap allows it to easily fit over body armor, web gear, hydration systems, and other mission-essential equipment. Galco’s positioning of the front strap attachment offers better balance, safer muzzle orientation and easier traversing capability than other three-point slings on the market today.

The BATTL Sling includes a Fastex Release Buckle on the Main Strap that enables the user to instantly remove the sling and shotgun. This allows detachment of the slung shotgun in the event of an emergency.

title: Want To Buy:  9mm/.45/.380 ammo and small/large pistol primers
postcontent:
Looking through these listings, seeing what people are asking for their ammo, my first reaction is anger.  But as I continue thinking about it, I get sincerely sad about it all.  Right now there is an unprecedented demand for ammo and reloading supplies.  People are in Panic Mode, afraid of what Obama might do.  So we have folks running out and stockpiling ammo.  To use? No.  To save? Nope.  To resell it for 2, 3, even 4 times what they paid for it?  YEP.  And individuals aren't the only ones doing it! I've been to several stores that are doing it, too!! People would counter that this is what a free-market, capitalistic society should expect.  But those people obviously have ZERO clue what they're talking about.  Seems in this world we live in, when demand increases, price increases.  When demand decreases, price....increases.  But what bothers me most about this is that we're doing it to one another.  At a time when it would behoove us to come together as a community, to appear as a unified group, we're too busy trying to fleece one another on ammo.  Forget ever being able to come together against a government if we ever needed to, we can't even keep from ripping each other off! We get outraged when the government does this kind of stuff with us - and, yet, here we are, doing it to one another.  What a shame.  Those of you asking ridiculous prices for ammo, you are no friend to those of us that truly believe in the constitutional right to bear arms.  Your motivation isn't "rights" or liberty, it's greed.  And anyone that would financially rape people they call brothers is not a good person.  Not someone I want standing beside me.  And for what? You're not making millions off of this!! What would a man give in exchange for his soul - a few boxes of ammo evidently.  Make no mistake, money and power do not change people - they simply reveal who those people really were all along.  And some of you, the first chance you got to jump in and profit off of us, you took it.  You betrayed your own for a few dollars, you Judas. 

I don't expect anything I've said to sway anyone either.  I'm under no illusions that the people who SHOULD feel guilty WILL feel guilty.  They've already proven that they are not guided by a moral compass but by a financial one.  6 months from now, a year from now - when all of this craziness has subsided (and people realize that nothing is going to fundamentally change) - you will have made a few extra bucks.  And proven your character.  And the rest of us will know that when it really counts, you cannot be counted on.  Well, not unless there's money in it for you.  

And to those of you like me, please don't buy from these idiots.  This shortage will subside and, eventually, be over with.  Or buy from those that charge you the same today as they did 6 months ago - there are still some good people (and businesses) out there.  Those are the folks I'm proud to align myself with.  Those are the people I'm trying to raise my 2 sons to be like.  God bless.
